parameters: Umi: "Mia... she collapsed when I woke up in the morning!"
Kru: "Is she sick? Has this ever happened before?"
Umi: "It's the first time... Mia is always energetic."
Kru: "I'll go consult with the chief for a bit!"
Kru: "Umi... I heard from the chief... You can't leave the forest?"
Umi: "Umi thinks she has to do something about it."

Kru: "Despite facing such a tough situation, you're trying to persevere and
overcome it."

Umi: "Umi is weak... But the reason I think about becoming stronger is
because of Mia..."

Umi: "Yes. Ever since Toto and Kaka disappeared, Umi couldn't speak
anymore... It was very troubling..."

Umi: "At that time, Umi met Mia in the forest. Mia was just a kitten and
very weak, and Umi thought she had to do something about it, and then
somehow strength welled up inside her..."

Umi: "After that, Umi was able to speak again... and became energetic to
raise Mia."
Kru: "I see... So the Umi we have now is all thanks to Mia, huh?"

Umi: "That's right... If it weren't for Mia, Umi would have remained sad
forever. I'm still sad, but now there are other feelings too..."

Umi: "Like being happy with Mia, or how delicious meat is, and also with
you..."

Umi: "Mmm... It's nothing. Anyway... I'm scared, but I'll go get that
herb."
Umi: "If I'm with you... I feel like I can do my best."
Kru: "It'll definitely be okay! I'm with you! Let's go!"
Umi: "This has become such a hassle."
Kru: "Is that what's-it-called cave really such a dangerous place?"
Umi: "The cave is far. Umi hates getting tired."
Kru: "Eh? You're not going? The chieftain will be angry, you know."
Umi: "Let the chieftain be angry. Umi hates the chieftain."

Kru: "No way, that's harsh. The chieftain doesn't seem like such a bad
person."

Umi: "The chieftain is a good person. Gives delicious things. Umi liked the
chieftain until yesterday. Today, Umi hates."
Kru: "Miss Umi, you're quite moody, aren't you?"

Umi: "Mia... don't be so mad... I apologize for speaking ill of the
chieftain."
Umi: "Sigh, understood. I'll go to the cave."
Kru: "Eh! Mia said that? And you listen to Mia..."

Umi: "Mia is Umi's family. Umi listens to what Mia says. Mia listens to
what Umi says."

Kru: "I don't quite understand, but thank you. I owe you for your
hospitality."
Umi: "Sigh. The southern exit of the village. From there, head west."
Umi: "Lies. You did well. Here, have some juice."
Kru: "Phew------!! A drink after a job well done is the best!!"
Kru: "What's up? What are you talking about?"
Umi: "You don't need to understand. Now..."
Umi: "I'm going to prepare the meat... Just wait until dinner."
Umi: "Umi likes to eat. So I like to cook too."
Kru: "I see, it comes naturally then. I'm looking forward to it."
Umi: "You can look forward to it. We got some good meat."
Umi: "Thanks to you, Kru. Thank you."
Kru: "Oh, yeah. Well, we both worked hard. It's nothing."

Kru: (Somehow... maybe it's because our chests touched. My heart's
racing...)
Kru: (And... being thanked by Umi somehow makes me... happy...)
Umi: "Well then, Umi is busy. You go get some fresh air outside."
Kru: "Yeah. I'll go for a bit."
Umi: "How was everyone in the village?"
Umi: "Kru, are you tired? Let's call it a day and rest."
